comments:
Transferred from Gloucestershire to Warwickshire on 1.4.1935. 
    See also Table 2, notes (c) and (d).

Created 1.4.1935 out of the parishes of Great Barrington, Little 
    Barrington and Eastleach Turville. See also Table 2, note (e).

Transferred from Worcestershire to Gloucestershire on 20.10.1844. 
    Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Icomb.

Transferred from Worcestershire to Gloucestershire on 1.4.1931. 
    Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Adelstrop.

Transferred from Worcestershire to Gloucestershire on 1.4.1931. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).
Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Upper Slaughter.

On 20.10.1844 the part in Berkshire  
    was transferred to Gloucestershire, so that thereafter Great Barrington was 
    entirely in Gloucestershire. Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of 
    Barrington. See also Table 2, note (a).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Ebrington. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and added to the parish of Batsford. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Swell and 
    Stow on the Wold.

Transferred from Gloucestershire to Warwickshire on 1.4.1935. 
    See also Table 2, notes (c) and (d).

Created 1.4.1935 from the parishes of Lower Swell and Upper Swell. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).

That part which until 1.4.1935 formed part of the parish of 
    Naunton. See also Table 2, note (f).

Abolished 1.4.1935 and divided between the parishes of Swell and 
    Stow on the Wold.
